<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-14T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-14T21:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/759: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spiker</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-15T10:00:00+08:00">December
                                    15, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 16—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>278. Referring to my No. 276, December 13, 2 p.m.,<note n="20" xml:id="d293fn20">This telegram reported the departure of a French
                                gunboat (893.0146/758).</note> and previous concerning withdrawal of
                            British and French gunboats from the Yangtze. British have ordered
                            withdrawal of three further gunboats from Shanghai-Hankow section of the
                            river, these including Hankow station ship H. M. S. <hi rend="italic">Peterel</hi> which departs December 18 leaving U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Guam</hi> as only non-Japanese gunboat here.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping, Chungking, Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Spiker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>